The paper deals with probabilistic databases and query evaluation techniques, which are core topics in the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Markov Logic Networks and the focus on correlations suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) as well. The paper also mentions approximation algorithms and offline compilation, which are relevant to the algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
